<subSubSection id="C3376551FFB3A85595D13502F344F87B" pageId="8" pageNumber="342" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9236DAFFB3A85595D13502F344F87B" blockId="8.[151,1437,716,2037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="342">
<emphasis id="B959EAC8FFB3A85595D13502F117F896" bold="true" box="[199,334,1868,1893]" pageId="8" pageNumber="342">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D59FFB3A85597263502F2E3F897" box="[560,698,1868,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Miritius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis id="B959EAC8FFB3A85597263502F2E3F897" box="[560,698,1868,1892]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="342">abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers probably to the presence of a marking drop-shaped in the first male abdominal ventrite that Bechyné paid attention.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
